Are you really using 2.1.1? If so, please retry with 2.1.2 - some fixes where made for hangs in Ole in 2.1.2 which may be causing your problem Sorry for the confusion, I am indeed using 2.1.1 with Excel 2002 SP-1, the modified problem statement is explained again here (Note : The following behavior is same in SWT 2.1.2 as well) :
Case 1: If I open a .csv (comma separated format) file in the Editor along with a text editor, we can reproduce the problem I have stated in the original bug report.
Case 2: If I open a .xls file in the Editor along with a text editor, then the menus function properly, though the display process has some flicker.
Case 3: (This is a new addition) If I open a .xls, a .csv and a text file, then (a) .xls editor has its own Excel specific and Platform menus (appropriate) (b) .csv and text editors both have the menus pertaining to text editor. and (c) the .csv editor becomes uneditable sometimes showing row and column headers and sometimes not.
How do you open the .csv file - are you writing your own editor or embedding another Ole object?
The problem is that you must be very careful about the order in which things become activated.
See:
https://bugs.eclipse.org/bugs/show_bug.cgi?id=17480
When an Ole editor is activated or deactivated it changes the menu shown. Therefore, if you are switching between two Ole editors you must deactivate the one that you are leaving before activating the one you are going to. The same is true when going between an Ole editor and a non-Ole editor. You need to deactivate the Ole Editor before you activate the text editor. The Eclipse Text editor gets it right and the Eclipse OleEditor gets it right - use those as your examples.
Got it, thx!
I was writing my own editor embedding OleFrame and expected OleFrame to take care of menus. A gross blunder on my part :(!!
But looks like .csv files can be opened in Excel by double clicking in WindowsExplorer, but do not get opened in OleEditor by doubleclicking in ResourceNavigator.
I can live with that for now... or can open a bug report if you suggest. Created attachment 7122 screenshot of creating file association
In Window -> Preferences update you file associations to map *.csv to Excel - see attached screen shot.
After you add *.csv to the top area, click on "Add" in the bototm area to create the association with Excel. Closing this bug report since menu is behaving as expected.

