Bug.WithStack:
Overview/Reproducing Procedure :
Create an editor with embedded Excel document. 
Double click on the Editor title tab to resize to occupy the whole workbench
page region. The Excel document's data region disappears.

But when the Eclipse shell is resized, we do not lose the data region.

Additional Information :
The code snippet used to embed the document :

	/**
	 * @see org.eclipse.ui.IWorkbenchPart#createPartControl(Composite)
	 */
	public void createPartControl(final Composite parent) {

		GridLayout layout = new GridLayout();
		layout.numColumns = 1;
		layout.marginHeight = 0;
		layout.marginWidth = 0;
		layout.verticalSpacing = 0;
		parent.setLayout(layout);

		OleFrame frame = new OleFrame(parent, SWT.NONE);

		GridData frameGridData = new GridData(GridData.FILL_BOTH);
		frameGridData.horizontalAlignment = GridData.FILL;
		frameGridData.verticalAlignment = GridData.FILL;
		frame.setLayoutData(frameGridData);
		
		frame.setSize(500, 500);

		String fullPath = editorInput.getFile().getLocation().toOSString();
		File file = new File(fullPath);
		OleClientSite clientSite = new OleClientSite(frame, SWT.BORDER, file);
		clientSite.doVerb(OLE.OLEIVERB_PRIMARY);
		
		parent.setSize(parent.getSize());

	}
I'm unable to replicate this problem with Eclipse 3.3.
STEPS:
  - doubled clicked on an Excel document in the Package Explorer 
    to open an in-place-editor. 
  - double-clicked on the editor tab to "maximize" it
  - resized the Eclipse workbench
  - double-clicked on the editor tab to "restore" it
The Excel document appears to be working as expected.

